# Post-push: monitor GitHub Actions (binding)

**Non-negotiable.** If your turn includes **`git push`** (or any command that updates `origin`), you **do not** finish the task, **do not** tell the user the work is delivered, **do not** say ‚Äúcommit and push complete,‚Äù and **do not** move on until you have **monitored CI** as below.

Local `pnpm` / `turbo` / tests are **not** sufficient proof. GitHub Actions can still fail.

## Red flags (if you think this, you are wrong)

| Excuse | Reality |
|--------|---------|
| ‚ÄúThe user only asked to push‚Äù | Push is one step; **monitoring is part of the same push workflow.** |
| ‚ÄúI‚Äôll let them check Actions‚Äù | Forbidden unless `gh` is broken **and** you gave the Actions URL **and** said CI is unverified. |
| ‚ÄúTests passed locally‚Äù | Runners, Docker acceptance, docs, and permissions differ. |
| ‚ÄúThis was a small / docs-only change‚Äù | Still run the monitor; workflows you skip are the ones that fail. |
| ‚ÄúI already ran out of time / tokens‚Äù | Then **state CI is still pending** and give `gh run list` / URLs‚Äîdo not imply green. |

## Mandatory sequence (do not reorder)

1. **Push** (if not already done).
2. **Immediately** get the **branch** and **commit SHA** you pushed: `git rev-parse HEAD` (and branch if needed).
3. **List runs** for that branch: `gh run list --branch <branch> --limit 15` (or filter by commit in the UI).
4. For **this repository**, a push to **`main`** typically triggers **four** workflows on the **same `headSha`**. You must account for **all** that apply to that commit:
   - **`ci`** ‚Äî lint, typecheck, test:coverage, build, Go agent tests.
   - **`acceptance`** ‚Äî Docker Compose + `pnpm acceptance`.
   - **`docs`** ‚Äî Jekyll docs.
   - **`docs-site-www`** ‚Äî docs site build/deploy.
5. **Watch** every run that is `queued` or `in_progress` for that commit until **`completed`**, using **GitHub CLI** in this environment:
   - `gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status` per run, **or** poll `gh run list` until each workflow shows `conclusion` (not empty).
6. **Report outcomes** in your reply: each workflow name ‚Üí `success` or `failure` (or `skipped` / `cancelled` if shown). If **any** failed: `gh run view <id> --log-failed` when possible, summarize, fix, verify locally, commit, push, and **repeat this entire section from step 1**.

## If `gh` is unavailable or auth fails

- Say **explicitly** that you could not verify Actions.
- Give the pattern: `https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/actions` (resolve owner/repo from `git remote -v`).
- Do **not** say the branch is green.

## Repo note (remote name vs GitHub)

`git remote` may still say `service-monitor`; GitHub Actions for the same code may run under **`InnKeeperDevOps/kaiad`**. Use `gh run list` from the repo root‚Äî`gh` uses the **GitHub remote**‚Äîand verify runs match your **commit SHA**.

## Forbidden (repeated on purpose)

- Ending the turn right after push with only ‚Äúpushed‚Äù or ‚Äúdone.‚Äù
- Claiming delivery without listing workflow results for that commit.
- Skipping **acceptance** or **docs** because ‚Äúonly `ci` matters.‚Äù
